        "title": "배열 추가문제2",
        "excerpt":"Question 1: Container With Most Water   You are given an integer array height of length n. There are n vertical lines drawn such that the two endpoints of the ith line are (i, 0) and (i, height[i]).   Find two lines that together with the x-axis form a container, such that the container contains the most water.   Return the maximum amount of water a container can store.   Notice that you may not slant the container.   입력: height = [1,8,6,2,5,4,8,3,7]  출력: 49   내 풀이   class Solution:     def maxArea(self, height: List[int]) -&gt; int:         left, right = 0, len(height) - 1         distance = len(height) - 1             max_volume = 0                  for d in range(distance, 0, -1):             if height[left] &lt; height[right]:                 max_volume = max(height[left] * d, max_volume)                 left += 1             else:                 max_volume = max(height[right] * d, max_volume)                 right -= 1                  return max_volume      왼쪽 기둥과 오른쪽 기둥을 하나씩 비교해가며 낮은 높이의 기둥을 기둥사이의 거리만큼을 곱한 값을 max_volume으로 정의하였다.   결과   Runtime: 1016 ms, faster than 40.47% of Python3 online submissions for Container With Most Water. Memory Usage: 27.5 MB, less than 57.49% of Python3 online submissions for Container With Most Water.    ","categories": ["algorithm","python"],
